 Efforts by Bethelsdorp police in cracking down on the illicit sale of drugs continue to yield positive results. "While members were busy in Coleus Street, Sanctor with crime prevention duties the members noticed two men running towards a well-known drug post," said spokesperson, Capt Sandra Janse Van Rensburg. "The members managed to arrest the two suspects, aged 22 and 36 years, and confiscated drugs such tik, mandrax, cocaine and dagga, from the suspects." The suspects will appear in court on charges of possession of drugs at the Gelvandale Magistrate's Court on Monday. 